The paper deals with attacks on state estimation in power grids, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of graph-cut based formulations, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the manipulation of meter measurements, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI).
